Spatial data IO between Python and R¶

scDIOR supports spatial omics data IO between R and Python platforms.

3.1. In this script, we load the spatial data, analyse data by Scanpy and covert the result to the h5 file¶

In [1]:
# import
import scanpy as sc
import diopy
import h5py
import anndata
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import scipy
import scvelo as scv
import os
%matplotlib inline

Loading data¶

In [2]:
# set path file
datafile = '../../data/3.spatial_analysis_data'
resultfile = '../../result/3.spatial_analysis_result'
if not os.path.isdir(resultfile):
    os.makedirs(resultfile)
In [3]:
# reading data
adata = sc.read('%s/adata_fig3c.h5ad'%datafile)

Spatial omic analysis¶

In [4]:
sc.pp.filter_cells(adata, min_counts=5000)
sc.pp.filter_cells(adata, max_counts=35000)
adata = adata[adata.obs["pct_counts_mt"] < 20]
print(f"#cells after MT filter: {adata.n_obs}")
sc.pp.filter_genes(adata, min_cells=10)

#cells after MT filter: 3962

Trying to set attribute `.var` of view, copying.
In [5]:
sc.pp.normalize_total(adata, inplace=True)
sc.pp.log1p(adata)
sc.pp.highly_variable_genes(adata, flavor="seurat", n_top_genes=2000)
In [6]:
sc.pp.pca(adata)
sc.pp.neighbors(adata)
sc.tl.umap(adata)
sc.tl.leiden(adata, key_added="clusters")
In [7]:
# plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (4, 4)
sc.settings.set_figure_params(dpi=150,facecolor='white')
sc.pl.umap(adata, color=["total_counts", "n_genes_by_counts", "clusters"], wspace=0.4)
In [8]:
# Visualization base on the spatial coordinate
sc.settings.set_figure_params(dpi=150,facecolor='white')
sc.pl.spatial(adata, img_key="hires", color=["clusters", "CR2"])

Saving data by diopy¶

Now, we switch to 3.2.spatial_data_from_scanpy_to_seurat.ipynb for data analysis again.

In [9]:
diopy.output.write_h5(adata = adata, 
                      file = '%s/adata_fig3c.h5'%resultfile,
                      assay_name='spatial')
